Title: Cylinder Seal with Seated Deity, Worrshipper, and Inscriptions
Description: The depicted scene features an interceding goddess in a long tufted robe and horned headdress, with one arm raised, leading a worshipper before a seated deity in long, tufted robe, and a horned headdress. The field between the seated deity and interceding goddess includes an inverted crescent. The scene is framed with a cuneiform inscription in two registers.
Provenance: Sadie Jones (Mrs. Henry Walters), New York [date and mode of acquisition unknown]; Sale, Joseph Brummer, New York, 1941; Walters Art Museum, 1941, by purchase.
Creator: Near Eastern
